testspeednet.net.utils.printer.printer(text: str, quiet: bool = False, debug: bool = False, error: bool = False, **kwargs: Any) → None[source]¶

Prints formatted text to standard output or standard error.

Parameters:

  • text (<str>) – The text to be printed

  • quiet (<bool>) – If True, suppresses printing (default: False)

  • debug (<bool>) – If True, prefixes text with ‘DEBUG:’ (default: False)

  • error (<bool>) – If True, prints to standard error instead of standard output

  • kwargs (<Any>) – Additional keyword arguments passed to print_private
